	<h2>No 1 Dad sports cup</h2>


	<p>This simple sports cup is made from a plastic disposable wine glass sprayed gold. The colours can easily be altered to match dads’ favourite sports teams or colours.</p>


	<p><strong>Skills:</strong> ICT; cutting; gluing</p>


	<p><strong>You will need:</strong> plastic wine glasses; gold spray paint; pipe cleaners; glue; sticky tape; computer and printer; thin red and white card; red crêpe paper; small plastic bag and sweets.</p>


	<p>1. Prepare the sprayed wine glasses prior to the lesson. Allow to dry fully.</p>


	<p>2. Bend two pipe cleaners into handle shapes and glue or tape one to each side of the cup.</p>


	<p>3. Using a computer, print the words, ‘No 1 <span class="caps">DAD</span>’, on a red background, onto thin card. Cut into a circle shape about 4cm in diameter. Cut a second circle of red card the same size.</p>


	<p>4. Cut a 4cm x 50cm strip of crêpe paper and fold in half all along the length. Fold the paper in a fanned concertina to create a circle. (Alternatively, glue can be added to the outside edges of the plain circle. Attach the end of the crêpe paper strip and scrunch it. Continue around the circle, creating a frilly edge.)</p>


	<p>5. Place glue around the edge of the plain circle and secure to the back of the folded crêpe paper frill. Glue the message circle to the front.</p>


	<p>6. Cut two 7cm long stripes of crêpe paper, with forked ends, and glue to the back of the rosette. Glue the rosette to the front of the cup. Fill a small bag with sweets, tie with curling ribbon and pop into the cup.</p>


