	<h2><span class="caps">DIY</span> Dad frame</h2>


	<p>This frame design can be adapted to suit different hobbies. Make a green surround and add a football and boots, or a black surround with white central lines and racing car accents.</p>


	<p><strong>SKills:</strong> cutting; drawing; measuring</p>


	<p><strong>You will need:</strong> thick card; scissors; ruler; paper fasteners; glue; beige, white, red and blue fun foam; silver sticky-backed plastic; pinking shears and a black pen.</p>


	<p>1. Cut two rectangles of thick card measuring 7.5cm x 10.5cm. Cut a deep U shape (roughly 9.5cm x 5.5cm) into one, leaving a three-sided frame. Glue together.</p>


	<p>2. Cut two pieces of beige fun foam measuring 11.5cm x 1.5cm and two measuring 9cm x 1.5cm. Draw on pen lines to look like wooden planks. Overlap the ‘planks’ at the corners to create a frame and fix with paper fasteners to look like nails. Glue to the front of the U-shaped frame.</p>


	<p>3. Cut a strip of thick card measuring 2cm x 7.5cm. Score 2cm from the top and fold. Glue to the back of the frame to make a stand.</p>


	<p>4. Cut out tool shapes from fun foam. Cover white fun foam in silver sticky-backed plastic for the metal parts of the tools. Cut fringing for the brush bristles and using pinking shears for the saw teeth.</p>


	<p>5. Glue each tool together and stick in place on the frame. Ensure that the space to insert the photograph is at the top.</p>

